Spring Street, north side, from Wooster Street to, but not including, West Broadway (formerly South Fifth Avenue). Na. 143 Spring Street is the frame house on the N.W. corner of Wooster Street. No. 147, the loft building between thc two taller ones, is an example of brick building faced with iron.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 557.
